{"_type":"memory","key":"acdc-2d-u-net-baseline-40ep-no-aug","value":"ACDC 2D U-Net baseline (40ep, no aug, 80/20 patient split): VAL Dice LV-cav 0.927, LV-myo 0.814, RV 0.843, mean 0.861; EF MAE 4.5%. Worst = HCM (EF d up to 16% - thick myo boundary). Run: pytorch_training_env python -m cardioseg.training.train --acdc. Near-SOTA on LV-cav; myo/RV have headroom (aug, more epochs)."}
{"_type":"memory","key":"acdc-label-encoding-verified-on-real-masks-geometric","value":"ACDC label encoding VERIFIED on real masks (geometric myo-enclosure test): 0=bg, 1=RV cavity, 2=LV myocardium, 3=LV cavity. LV is label 3, NOT 1. synth.py + measure.py originally had lv_label=1 (would compute RV EF) — fixed to 3. Always disambiguate LV vs RV geometrically (src/data/mri/identify_lv_cavity), never trust a remembered int. Real ACDC: spacing z=10mm in-plane ~1.4-1.6mm, anisotropy 6-7x, intensity uncalibrated. DCM patients EF 10-29% (validates fix)."}
